1
00:00:04,380 --> 00:00:08,199
You know, I don't think people would believe it, but I think it's self-taught.

2
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:12,500
I don't think confidence is something that you are born with.

3
00:00:12,980 --> 00:00:15,640
I don't think confidence is, it's a skill set.

4
00:00:16,239 --> 00:00:18,760
And I had no confidence growing up.

5
00:00:18,839 --> 00:00:22,500
As a child, I had very low self-esteem.

6
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,640
I was gawky as a teenager.

7
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:25,640
I lived in America.

8
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:29,379
I was made to feel conscious about the fact that I was Indian.

9
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,519
That was weird at that time.

10
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:37,960
And not by everyone, but just by like a few bullies at school that hated me.

11
00:00:38,020 --> 00:00:39,140
High school is hard for everyone.

12
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:43,280
But so I was in a very weird sort of teenage place.

13
00:00:44,020 --> 00:00:47,079
And when Miss India happened, I mean, inherently competitive.

14
00:00:47,759 --> 00:00:53,420
I think the fact that I was competitive pushed me to teach myself to be confident.

15
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:55,799
Initially, I faked it until I made it.

16
00:00:56,479 --> 00:00:59,340
I was just like, I'm not going to let anyone see that I'm scared.

17
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:02,280
I'm not going to let anyone see that I'm affected.

18
00:01:02,460 --> 00:01:07,739
And over time, I realized like as a woman, as a girl in this world,

19
00:01:08,519 --> 00:01:13,040
if I allow myself to be hurt or if I allow myself to be affected,

20
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,819
that's all I'm going to be.

21
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:19,379
And I'm not trying to say that it's an issue that just women have.

22
00:01:19,819 --> 00:01:21,640
It's not easy to be a woman and show business.

23
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:24,439
And especially a woman who's opinionated, especially someone who,

24
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:28,400
I'm not, I'm sort of like, and I wasn't like that from the beginning.

25
00:01:28,819 --> 00:01:29,420
I sort of learned.

26
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,239
So confidence is something I taught myself over the years.

27
00:01:32,439 --> 00:01:35,159
I started becoming okay with who I am.

28
00:01:35,359 --> 00:01:37,180
I became the best version of me.

29
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:40,519
And then I sort of said, I'm okay.

30
00:01:40,859 --> 00:01:41,540
You know, I'm all right.

31
00:01:41,719 --> 00:01:43,780
Even if someone else thinks this, I'm okay.

32
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:45,379
And everyone can do that.

33
00:01:45,819 --> 00:01:46,959
People just don't realize that.

34
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:50,000
I was always creative in school, but I didn't know what to do with it.

35
00:01:50,519 --> 00:01:53,260
I used to write, I did plays, I would do school,

36
00:01:53,260 --> 00:01:56,099
but my aspiration was never to be creative.

37
00:01:56,659 --> 00:02:00,359
And now that I found this vocation, I'm producing, I write columns,

38
00:02:00,819 --> 00:02:04,319
my creativity comes out in whatever way it can.

39
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:08,280
And I think somehow something guides you.

40
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:09,819
What that is, I don't know.

41
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:10,740
I don't have a name for it.

42
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:11,539
I don't think it's a religion.

43
00:02:11,719 --> 00:02:12,599
I don't know if it's God.

44
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:13,659
I don't know what it is.

45
00:02:14,219 --> 00:02:15,740
I think something is bigger than us.

46
00:02:16,139 --> 00:02:16,879
And I believe in that.

47
00:02:16,879 --> 00:02:21,979
Well, when I became Miss India, I sort of was on strange ground myself

48
00:02:21,979 --> 00:02:25,979
because I was literally, I was in college, I was studying.

49
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,400
And now I'm suddenly Miss World.

50
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:31,599
And I have these, I was traveling all over the world, you know,

51
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,860
being an ambassador.

52
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:36,740
And suddenly, movie offers started coming to me from India.

53
00:02:36,939 --> 00:02:40,080
Because I think producers thought that it would make business sense to,

54
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:42,939
you know, have Miss World in the movie.

55
00:02:43,539 --> 00:02:45,000
And I guess it did.

56
00:02:45,659 --> 00:02:48,919
Because in my first, second films, like I won a lot of awards,

57
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,439
I didn't think I could act.

58
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:54,860
I just went in there with the idea of, okay, I can learn a new skill set.

59
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:58,219
I may not know what acting is about, but I can learn.

60
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,819
So that's how I taught myself.

61
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:01,979
I've never been to film school.

62
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:05,060
I taught my career has been in my film school.

63
00:03:05,259 --> 00:03:07,259
I've fallen down and dusted myself off.

64
00:03:07,699 --> 00:03:09,280
I've been okay to fail.

65
00:03:09,919 --> 00:03:11,340
I don't like failure.

66
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:14,039
I'll never let the same failure happen to me again.

67
00:03:14,199 --> 00:03:15,060
Because I learn from it.

68
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:16,460
I like knowledge.

69
00:03:17,599 --> 00:03:19,819
I like learning from the people around me.

70
00:03:20,060 --> 00:03:23,979
And I don't think anyone reaches a point no matter how successful you are in life,

71
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,840
or you can't learn something again.

72
00:03:26,319 --> 00:03:29,599
And I think that sort of got me to where I am.

73
00:03:29,939 --> 00:03:31,699
And that's been a big part of my work as a thing.

74
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:34,000
I remember when no one wanted to ask me a thing.

75
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:36,319
And I get that.

76
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:39,460
I remember when, and I still am.

77
00:03:39,460 --> 00:03:41,300
Like sometimes there's so many fights that I do.

78
00:03:41,419 --> 00:03:45,719
But I remember when nobody wanted to do, you know, want in my opinion.

79
00:03:45,939 --> 00:03:51,819
Or I remember when I had to work on, when I was just the side chick to the guy.

80
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:57,939
And I had to work and do small but important significant parts to prove that I can.

81
00:03:58,099 --> 00:03:58,539
And I will.

82
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,319
And then try.

83
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:01,400
So no one can be that.

84
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,099
You can't be like, oh, Destiny's going to knock on my door one day.

85
00:04:04,259 --> 00:04:04,860
No, it won't.

86
00:04:05,159 --> 00:04:07,219
You have to be able to recognize opportunities.

87
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:11,120
Because there'll be a lot of them that come into your life.

88
00:04:11,319 --> 00:04:13,960
And once you recognize an opportunity, you have to seize the day.

89
00:04:14,460 --> 00:04:15,879
And work and bloody hard.

90
00:04:16,019 --> 00:04:17,939
Because there'll be 25 other people you want to do.

91
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:21,480
I was told that I wanted because of confidence.

92
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:25,279
Because I asked later, there was so many more beautiful women than me.

93
00:04:25,779 --> 00:04:27,579
But of course, I was curious.

94
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:29,379
So I was like, well, what is it?

95
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,800
And they were like, just, even you speak, you're just eloquent and confident.

96
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:37,000
And I was 18 and I realized how important it was.

97
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:40,519
And I was in this world at 18, just because I was confident.

98
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:46,399
So it made me understand that confidence truly is the key to getting ahead in life.

99
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,639
If you believe in yourself, the world will believe in you.

100
00:04:49,079 --> 00:04:50,639
Because perception is reality.

101
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:07,259
And I realized that confidence is reality.

